  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: erigon/v2.47.0-stable-5536d645/linux-amd64/go1.20.5\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\nCommit hash: 5536d645\r\n\r\nErigon Command (with flags/config):\r\n--authrpc.jwtsecret=/jwt.hex\r\n--authrpc.addr=0.0.0.0\r\n--authrpc.vhosts=*\r\n--ws\r\n--datadir=/erigon-data\r\n--prune=htc\r\n--maxpeers=10\r\n\r\nConcensus Layer: Nimbus\r\n\r\nConcensus Layer Command (with flags/config):\r\n      --el=\"ws://erigon:8551\"\r\n      --el=\"ws://geth:8551\"\r\n      --jwt-secret=/home/user/nimbus-eth2/build/data/jwt.hex\r\n      --data-dir=/home/user/nimbus-eth2/build/data\r\n      --enr-auto-update:true\r\n      --num-threads=4\r\n      --rest\r\n      --rest-address=0.0.0.0\r\n      --rest-allow-origin=*\r\n      --metrics\r\n      --metrics-address=\"0.0.0.0\"\r\n      --doppelganger-detection=false\r\n      --status-bar=false\r\n      --max-peers=30\r\n\r\nChain/Network: Ethereum mainnet\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nErigon should wait until all block bodies have been downloaded \r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nErigon downloads block headers, but if not all have been delivered after 100 seconds it will restart from scratch. This process has been running for quite a while now.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nStart Erigon after some downtime, so that the number of missing blocks is too high and they cannot be downloaded within 100 seconds\r\n\r\n[erigon-logs.txt](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/files/11834046/erigon-logs.txt)\r\n\r\n",
